    "52,53.The previously described scenario is no longer applicable, as demonstrated below.",
    "Modern-day (quantum) learning models display good generalization performance while being able to completely overfit the data.",
    "This phenomenon is sometimes linked to the ability of learning models to memorize data.",
    "The term memorization is defined here as the occurrence of overfitting without concurrent generalization.",
    "It is essential to clarify that overfitting, in this context, means perfect fitting of the training set, regardless of its generalization performance."
